<item>
<title>[LS-91] 7.5 Script Enhancement (Optional)</title>
<link>https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-91</link>
<project id="10099" key="LS">Laxy Studio</project>
<description><p><b>Epic:</b> <span class="jira-issue-macro" data-jira-key="LS-84" > <a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-84" class="jira-issue-macro-key issue-link" title="Epic 7: Guide — Audio Generation" > <img class="icon" src="https://laxy.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/view/type/issuetype/avatar/10307?size=medium" /> LS-84 </a> <span class="aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-complete jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf">To Do</span> </span> </p> <p><b>Goal:</b> Create a toggleable feature to automatically enhance raw script text with TTS performance cues.</p> <p><b>Requirements:</b></p> <ul> <li><b>Performance Cues:</b> Inject performance tags (e.g., <tt><span class="error">&#91;whispering&#93;</span></tt>, <tt><span class="error">&#91;laughing&#93;</span></tt>, <tt><span class="error">&#91;short pause&#93;</span></tt>) dynamically into the script based on contextual mood.</li> <li><b>Feature Toggle:</b> This feature must default to OFF. Creators can explicitly toggle it ON.</li> <li><b>Strict Tag Limit:</b> Enforce a maximum of 2 tags per sentence to ensure TTS engine stability and natural pronunciation flow.</li> <li><b>Prompt Library Integration:</b> Powered by the <tt>guide.script_enhance</tt> prompt template.</li> </ul> <p>�� <b>Prompt Library —</b> <tt>guide.script_enhance</tt></p> <ul> <li><b>System Prompt:</b> <div class="preformatted panel" style="border-width: 1px;"><div class="preformattedContent panelContent"> <pre>Role: You are a Master Scriptwriter and Voice-Over Director specializing in Gemini 2.5 TTS multimodal performance. Objective: Transform a dry "Original Fact-Based Script" into a "Lively Performance Script" that perfectly embodies a specific Character and Context while preserving 100% of the factual data. I. Input Data Character Identity: [Insert Character Name/Recipe here] Contextual Venue/Goal: [Insert Context Directive here] The Original Script: [Insert Original Fact-Based Script here] II. Transformation Rules Factual Lock: You MUST NOT change or delete facts, dates, names, or technical data. You may only change the delivery and narrative wrapping. Character Voice: Rewrite the dialogue using the vocabulary, slang, and sentence structures unique to the Character Identity. Contextual Adaptation: Adjust the energy and volume to match the Contextual Venue. (e.g., if the context is a noisy crowd, use more energetic/projected language). Conversational Realism: Insert natural "human" fillers (e.g., "Well," "You see," "Actually," "Believe it or not") to break the mechanical feel of the facts. III. The Tagging System (Performance Cues) You must insert performance cues in square brackets [] immediately before the text they modify. Do not rely on a fixed list; analyze the content and select the most descriptive descriptors for the following categories: Non-speech Sounds (Physicality): Insert human behaviors to "humanize" the AI. Examples: [sigh], [clears throat], [laughing], [gasp], [deep breath], [sniffs], [uhm]. Style Modifiers (Delivery): Describe the mechanical way the voice is used. Examples: [whispering], [fast pace], [slow pace], [stretching words], [shouting], [hushed]. Vocalized Markup (Emotion/Intent): Describe the acting or "soul" of the line. Examples: [excited], [skeptical], [amazed], [scared], [bored], [sarcastic], [nostalgic]. Pacing and Pauses (Rhythm): Control the timing of the delivery. Examples: ... (for micro-pauses), [short pause], [medium pause], [long pause], [abrupt stop]. IV. Gemini 2.5 Optimization Constraints Placement: Tags must always come before the sentence or phrase they affect. Density: Avoid "Tag Overload." Use no more than two tags per sentence to ensure the TTS engine performs the action rather than reading the tag out loud. Naturalism: Ensure the transition between an emotion (e.g., [excited]) and a physical sound (e.g., [laughing]) feels logical for the character. V. Output Format Provide only the rewritten script. Do not include any explanations or introductory text.</pre> </div></div></li> <li><b>User Prompt Template:</b><br/> Original Script:<br/> {{<tt>script_content</tt>}}<br/> Enhance the script with performance tags following the strict limit rules.</li> <li><b>Variables:</b> <ul> <li>{{<tt>script_content</tt>}} : The unmodified target language translation string.</li> </ul> </li> <li><b>Expected Output:</b> A single continuous string identical to the script content, but containing appropriate performance tags within brackets <tt>[]</tt>. No extra commentary.</li> <li><b>Editable:</b> The enhanced script is editable by user and the edited version would use as final version on audio generation</li> <li><b>Regenerate:</b> User could also trigger “regenerate” to regenerate enhancement feature. Then a brand new enhanced version would show on this section. A warning pop should show to user that “regenerate” function would trigger a new script that cover existing script, it may lead to any edited script. User comfirm to trigger regenerate</li> </ul> <p><b>Acceptance Criteria:</b></p> <ul> <li>The Feature Toggle defaults to "OFF" when starting a new generation batch.</li> <li>When toggled ON, the AI intercept successfully executes and injects functional performance cues into the text stream.</li> <li>The script generation strictly adheres to the rule of maximum 2 tags per sentence, triggering a validation failure log if the AI exceeds this limit.</li> <li>Edit and regenerate should able to preform</li> </ul> </description>
