<comment id="12019" author="712020:8c1c869b-c4be-4401-b6c0-3f69c6178d55" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:32:12 +0900"><ul> <li>When toggle is ON, should enhancement run automatically during generate, or should user click a separate “enhance/regenerate” action first?</li> <li>Scope is unclear: enhancement applies per whole script, per POI, or per POI-language?</li> <li>The prompt body references Character Identity and Contextual Venue, but the user prompt only passes <tt>script_content</tt>. Should character/director-note actually be inputs?</li> <li>If AI exceeds the “max 2 tags per sentence” rule, should generation be blocked, warning-only, or auto-corrected?</li> <li>If user manually edits the enhanced script and exceeds tag limits, do we allow it or validate/block it?</li> <li>“Regenerate” says overwrite current edited script after warning, but it does not say whether previous edited versions are preserved in history.</li> </ul> </comment>
